==English==

===Etymology===
From [[w:Latin|Latin]] ''[[divide et impera]]''

===Phrase===
{{infl|en|phrase}}

# A combination of political, military and economic strategies that aim to gain and maintain power by breaking up larger concentrations of power into chunks that individually have less power than the one implementing the strategy.
# {{computing}} Applied to various [[algorithm]]s, such as [[quicksort]], that solve a problem by splitting it [[recursive]]ly into smaller problems until all of the remaining problems are [[trivial]].

